HACK: How I made my $10 roses looks like $100 and hold for over two weeks in ten seconds 🤍 One of my absolute favorite ‘everyday luxury’ treats is to have fresh flowers at home.. But I’m not always feeling like spending too much 💰 since most flowers only hold up for several days. Here is some hacks to make them last longer:

1. Change water every third day 💦 

2. When changing water you HAVE TO make a new cut.. The cut is where the flower breath basically and it easily clogs. Always use a 🔪 and NEVER a ✂️ !!

3. Save and enjoy for later 🤍

As you all might know I am very interested in airplanes and are studying for my #PPL so when this invite damp down my mailbox my face went 😁 Last week I was invited by @flexjetinc to Bromma Airport to a private viewing of their stunning mid-size business jet Praetor 600. The aircraft is made by Brazilian manufacturer @embraer, has a stand up cabin (I’m 174 and I could stand straight) and it’s flown by wire (which I love as it’s easier to maneuver in rough conditions and makes it easier to land at smaller airports). This particular configuration fits nine passengers (if you use the sofa), one cabin crew and two pilots.. The Praetor 600 has a range of approx 8hrs depending on weight which takes you from London to New York in a (very) comfortable way ✈️ #flexjet

Who would say no to an extra shot of Grain de Café to their daily coffee? Well, not me…

Today I was invited by wonderful and talanted @lisa.brormann at @cartier to view their latest collection; Grain de Café. 

In 1956, Audrey Hepburn wore a pair of Cartier's Grain de Café earrings from Grain de Café collection that originates from 1938 under the creative direction of Jeanne Toussaint. ‘Find beauty in the unexpected’ was Toussaints mantra for the collection with an actual coffee bean as the inspiration for the collection. 

Some of you might recognize the necklace that was seen on not only Hepburn but Grace Kelly. The current collection is inspired by the glamour of the 1950s French Riviera with the radiant beauty of Grace Kelly (and she wore the necklace on Monaco’s postage stamp in 1957, see last picture). 

My absolute favorites was the earrings and the necklace. Cartier will be launching eight Grain de Café jewellery pieces available from June 2023.

Out of all @cartier stores in Europe, Stockholm is one of five stores having the privilege to show the stunning high jewelry collection ‘Architecture & Purity’ by @cartier and yesterday I was invited to an exclusive showing (and I had the privilege to see and try it in as well) and wow!

A collection inspired by architectural pieces that are full of light — the creations are built from an interplay of gems. For Cartier, the quest for purity lies at the heart of the creative process and the goal? To liberate the gemstone’s radiance.

Through the choice of diamond cuts, often geometric and calibrated, the light is reflected infinitely and is multiplied by the graphic structure of the design. Something you clearly could see when inspecting the first necklace I’m wearing inspired by a waterfall where the round diamonds are cut in a old technique making them slightly higher and even more unique. 

The second necklace is my absolute favorite and I instantly got drawn to the piece waking in the store. It says my name. Except for the minimalistic and sophisticated design, I love how the pear shaped diamond extends your neck when wearing.

Worth to notice: There is only one of each piece made ✨

Thank you team @cartier for having me 🤍 #cartier #ArchitectureandPurity

Frédéric Malle is still a very new perfume house to me but hearing the story behind I was very amazed about his passion and did you know his grandfather, Serge Hefler-Louiche, was the founder of Parfums Christian Dior?

The perfume house work as a classic publisher which is very unique. Under Frédéric’s guidance as a perfume publisher, who pushes perfumers to their creative limit and leads them into new olfactory territory, perfumers produce unique works of art sold under their own names. Together, the perfumers and publisher realize a vision of perfume as the masterful result of time, precision and true talent 🤍 #fredericmalle #heavencanwait

Come with us to Coral Adoption w. @velaacoralproject 🪸 

What’s the aims with the project?
🪸 To increase biodiversity 
🐠 Support marine conservation
🌊 To research methods to restoration that can be implemented across Maldives

And the methods? 🌴
🪸 Midwater and reef nurseries used for different species
🐚 Coral adoption provides one rope to the midwater nursery holding up to 10 corals that after a year will be transplanted back on to the reef using cement or frames
🐢 Biorock frames are in place since 2022 and using small electrical current to aid with mineral accretion that can speed up coral growth and improve recovery times from bleaching for example

What’s the benefits? 🤍
🐟 Contributes to a healthy reef and fish populations 
🏝️ Shoreline protection as frames and healthy reef structures absorb wave energy
⚡️ Create more resilient reefs in the face of human threats and global warming

Thank you @velaacoralproject for your outstanding work and dedication. Can’t wait to follow our corals journey 🪸🤍🐚🐠
